        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-9 multiple-edit-warning">
        <div class="alert alert-warning" id="warning-dd38ede5-0a2c-4204-948e-9ff3cd5af153">
            <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-info-sign"></span>This content has already been edited and is awaiting review.
        </div>
    </div>

        <div class="col-md-9 nohighlight member-container">
            <h2 class="memberLink col-md-9" id="member-link-dd38ede5-0a2c-4204-948e-9ff3cd5af153">
                Mr. R. A. Butler
            </h2>
        </div>
            <div class="col-md-3 hidden-sm hidden-xs right-column ">
            <a href="#contribution-dd38ede5-0a2c-4204-948e-9ff3cd5af153" rel="popover" class="link-to-contribution link-text" title="Share this contribution" data-placement="top"
               data-hop-url-shorten-url="/UrlShortener/ShorternUrl"
               data-hop-popover="http://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/1952-05-20/debates/f050ec40-abaa-49a3-b1bc-da676aa525d4/Clause31%E2%80%94(ChargeOfTheExcessProfitsLevy)#contribution-dd38ede5-0a2c-4204-948e-9ff3cd5af153">
                <div class="share-icon">&nbsp;</div><span class="share-text">Share</span>
            </a>
        </div>

    


    <div class="inner">
        <div class="col-md-9 contribution content-container">



<p class="">I think that would be going too far. There is nothing which offends if we take Clauses 31 and 32. Right hon. and hon. Gentlemen are perfectly competent to master the issues, and it is perfectly reasonable for us to consider the circumstances when we get into the sphere of the Amendments which have been put down too late. I do not doubt the right hon. Gentleman has made his suggestion in a perfectly good spirit, but it is unreasonable.<p></p> I think it would be much better to come to a decision on this and then proceed with Clauses 31 and 32 on the understanding that when we come to the situation when Amendments have to be considered which have not been long enough on the Order Paper, the right hon. Gentleman can move to report Progress and we can discuss the matter. That is perfectly reasonable, and I suggest that we should come to a decision now.</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
                        <a href="#contribution-dd38ede5-0a2c-4204-948e-9ff3cd5af153" rel="popover" class="link-to-contribution link-to-contribution-mobile link-text" title="Share this contribution" data-placement="top"
                           data-hop-url-shorten-url="/UrlShortener/ShorternUrl"
                           data-hop-popover="http://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/1952-05-20/debates/f050ec40-abaa-49a3-b1bc-da676aa525d4/Clause31%E2%80%94(ChargeOfTheExcessProfitsLevy)#contribution-dd38ede5-0a2c-4204-948e-9ff3cd5af153">
                            <div class="share-icon">&nbsp;</div>&nbsp;Share
                        </a>
                    </div>

        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="clearfix"></div>
</div>







