    <div class="inner">
        <div class="col-md-9 contribution content-container">



<p class="">Not at all. Either one has to acknowledge that the State can ignore the profits made out of the injection into the economy of re-armament—due to causes outside the private individual and private enterprise—or one has to recognise the economic fact of life which, no <span id="384" class="column-number" data-column-number="384"></span> doubt, the hon. Member for Gravesend (Sir R. Acland) is incapable of recognizing—that it is impossible to isolate the rearmament issue from general production. Once we have accepted the latter, we are bound to have a tax on the lines which we have here.</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
                        <a href="#contribution-429037f2-cc98-4838-9fa2-d284919cd6f5" rel="popover" class="link-to-contribution link-to-contribution-mobile link-text" title="Share this contribution" data-placement="top"
                           data-hop-url-shorten-url="/UrlShortener/ShorternUrl"
                           data-hop-popover="http://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/1952-05-20/debates/f050ec40-abaa-49a3-b1bc-da676aa525d4/Clause31%E2%80%94(ChargeOfTheExcessProfitsLevy)#contribution-429037f2-cc98-4838-9fa2-d284919cd6f5">
